#
# Custom recipe: SGLang v0.5.14 + SM121 sgl-kernel patches
#                + Gemma-4 NVFP4 source patch + DiffusionGemma dLLM (unmerged #28054).
#
# Tag: xomoxcc/dgx-spark-sglang:0.5.14-gemmadiffusion-sm121
#
# THE UNIFIED GEMMA-4 IMAGE. Serves ALL five Gemma-4 profiles off one build:
#   - BF16 + FROZEN_KV_MTP (google/gemma-4-31B-it, google/gemma-4-26B-A4B-it)
#   - NVFP4 (nvidia/Gemma-4-31B-IT-NVFP4, nvidia/Gemma-4-26B-A4B-NVFP4)
#   - DiffusionGemma dLLM (nvidia/diffusiongemma-26B-A4B-it-NVFP4)
#
# MOVED FROM THE 3a1417a DEV-PIN TO THE v0.5.14 TAG (2026-06-29):
#   This recipe was originally forward-pinned to main commit 3a1417a because
#   v0.5.13 lacked the FROZEN_KV_MTP fix (PR #28081) — Gemma-4 BF16 MTP died at
#   boot with "'NoneType' object has no attribute 'target_token_to_kv_pool'"
#   (kv_context is None). v0.5.14 (released 2026-06-26, commit 49e384ce) now
#   carries #28081 natively: git ancestry confirms #28081 is an ancestor of
#   v0.5.14 but NOT of v0.5.13 (v0.5.13 was cut from a diverging release branch).
#   So the forward-pin is no longer needed and SGLANG_REF moves to the clean tag.
#   EAGLE-v1 was removed upstream by #28129/#28133 (2026-06-13) and is therefore
#   already gone in v0.5.14 — we never used it, no impact.
#   STILL OPEN at v0.5.14: PR #28054 (DiffusionGemma) — the source patch stays
#   (see below). The v0.5.14 release notes cite "#27824 DiffusionGemma" but that
#   is only a cookbook/docs PR, NOT the model-support code.
#
# ⚠️  v0.5.14 is a tagged release but 248 commits past v0.5.13 (and past the old
#     3a1417a pin). The SM121 sgl-kernel source patches (always_source_patches:
#     sgl-kernel-sm121.patch et al.) were validated against the v0.5.13 tag and
#     are BEST-EFFORT here — drift in the sgl-kernel C++ source
#     (nvfp4_blockwise_moe.cuh / CMakeLists) is possible. The in-container
#     `patch --dry-run` gates this — if it FAILS, regenerate the failing
#     sgl-kernel patch against the v0.5.14 source tree before this recipe builds.
#
# The filename contains "gemma4" → build_sm121_image.sh applies the gemma4-NVFP4
# source patch (#22928 geglu-nan-clamp; inert on dense BF16, needed by NVFP4
# Gemma). The diffusiongemma Dockerfile patch anchors AFTER the gemma4 block, so
# this *gemma4* variant is required.
#
# Patches stacked (both still OPEN upstream):
#   - sglang-gemma4-geglu-nan-clamp.patch (PR #22928) — Gemma-4 GeGLU + FP4
#     block-scale NaN clamp (NVFP4 path; inert on BF16).
#   - sglang-diffusiongemma-pr28054.patch (PR #28054) — dLLM Gemma4Renoise +
#     gemma4_diffusion encoder-decoder model + diffusion_gemma processor.
#     Auf 0/entfernen, sobald #28054 im gepinnten SGLANG_REF enthalten ist.
#
# ⚠️  TRANSFORMERS: PR #28054 bumpt im pyproject transformers 5.8.1 → 5.11.0;
#     dieser Hunk ist im Source-Patch GESTRIPPT (sglang --no-deps; transformers
#     separat via TRANSFORMERS_VERSION). Falls DiffusionGemma mit AutoConfig-/
#     Modeling-Fehler nicht lädt: TRANSFORMERS_VERSION hier auf 5.11.0 heben.
#
DOCKERFILE=Dockerfile.sglang-nightly
TARGET=runtime

BASE_IMAGE=xomoxcc/dgx-spark-pytorch-dev:2.12.0-v1-cu132

# 0.6.13 (stable, released 2026-06-24; was 0.6.13rc2 — stable carries the same
# rc2 content). NB: flashinfer-attn stays UNUSABLE for Gemma4 (SGLang allowlist:
# trtllm_mha | triton | intel_xpu), so the PR #3576 head_dim=512 work is moot for
# Gemma attention; the bump only matters for the NVFP4 quant kernels.
FLASHINFER_VERSION=0.6.13

# 2026-06-20: auf 5.11.0 gehoben — 5.8.0 kennt model_type `diffusion_gemma` nicht
# (transformers CONFIG_MAPPING KeyError → "does not recognize this architecture" bei
# AutoConfig.from_pretrained; trust_remote_code hilft nicht, da das NVFP4-Repo keine
# auto_map/Remote-Config mitliefert). 5.11.0 ist die von PR #28054 gepinnte Version,
# in der die diffusion_gemma-Config nativ registriert ist. Betrifft das UNIFIED-Image
# → autoregressive Gemma-4-Profile (BF16/NVFP4/FROZEN_KV_MTP) auf 5.11.0 neu verifizieren.
TRANSFORMERS_VERSION=5.11.0

# kernels 0.14.1 — exakt SGLang v0.5.14s pyproject-Pin (kernels>=0.14.1,<0.15),
# bumped von 0.12.3. Perf-neutral für SM121 (der HF-Hub-Loader ist auf GB10 nicht
# im Hotpath; sgl-flash-attn3 ist via _is_fa3_supported deaktiviert und hat keine
# sm_121/ARM64-Builds). Detailbegründung: sglang-0.5.14-sm121.recipe.
KERNELS_VERSION=0.14.1

# v0.5.14 tag (released 2026-06-26, commit 49e384ce). SGLANG_VERSION >= 0.5.12 so
# the build SKIPS the Gemma-4 MTP cherry-pick (#24436 native since v0.5.12;
# re-applying would fail). #28081 (FROZEN_KV_MTP) and the EAGLE-v1 removal
# (#28129/#28133) are already in this tag — see the header.
SGLANG_VERSION=0.5.14
SGLANG_REF="v0.5.14"

# Main-ahead sgl-kernel patch variant. The mscclpp link refactor (dropped
# mscclpp_static from the common_ops_sm90/sm100 link lines + removed the
# mscclpp-build block) landed between v0.5.13 and 3a1417a and broke the canonical
# sgl-kernel-skip-sm90-target.patch (Hunk #3 FAILED at 398). v0.5.14 is 248
# commits past v0.5.13 (well past 3a1417a) and CONTAINS that refactor, so this
# flag MUST stay on even though SGLANG_REF is now a tagged release. It makes
# build_sm121_image.sh install the "-mainahead" patch siblings (regenerated
# against 3a1417a) under the canonical names where they exist (skip-sm90-target,
# diffusiongemma); the v0.5.13 recipes keep the originals. The in-container
# dry-run gates everything — if a -mainahead patch still fails against v0.5.14,
# regenerate it against the v0.5.14 source tree.
SGL_KERNEL_MAINAHEAD=1

# DiffusionGemma dLLM runtime — upstream PR #28054 (OPEN). Gated dockerfile-
# diffusiongemma.patch in build_sm121_image.sh::apply_patches (Schritt 2e).
APPLY_DIFFUSIONGEMMA_PR28054=1

IMAGE_TAG=xomoxcc/dgx-spark-sglang:0.5.14-gemmadiffusion-sm121
